The key insight is that `W` is defined using `Δ'` and `V` is defined using `Δ`. Since `Δ' ⊆ Δ`, every element in `W` must also be in `V`. The proof uses the definition of `Submodule.le_def` which requires showing that every element in `W` is also in `V`. This is done by taking an arbitrary element `x` in `W`, unfolding the definition of `W`, and then showing that `x` must also be in `V` using the fact that `Δ' ⊆ Δ`.

